In about 12 hours, there were three train accidents -- including the Chester crash -- in the United States on Sunday.
Amtrak initially said it was providing limited service between Philadelphia and Wilmington, Delaware, as the Federal Railroad Administration and NTSB investigate. A later statement said that trains will run as regularly scheduled but that there would be some delays between Philadelphia and Wilmington.
